ABUJA – The Supreme Court, on Friday held that the Executive Order 10 signed by President Muhammadu Buhari is unlawful and unconstitutional. The Apex court made the pronouncement while delivering judgment on the suit filed by the 36 States Government against the Federal Government on the funding of the Judiciary and the constitutionality of the Executive Order 10. The Executive Order 10 basically relates to the funding of State Judiciary and Legislature. Enugu LG Polls: APGA Chairman Charges ENSIEC On Free, Fair… FCT Council Polls: Police Withdraw Earlier Announced Curfew In a split judgment, six out of the seven-member panel agreed that the President exceeded his constitutional powers in issuing the Executive Order 10. All the seven jurists agreed that the States were not entitled to be refunded all they had expended before now to maintain those courts. The majority decision also stated that it was not the responsibility of the Federal Government to fund the capital and recurrent expenditures of the superior courts created for States under Section six of the Constitution.